eltMesErpsMIB.name: eltMesErpsMIB

revisions.description: Deprecate all objects in this module.

eltMesErpsMIB.description: The MIB module for managing Ethernet Ring Protection Switching.

EltErpsEnabledState.name: EltErpsEnabledState
EltErpsEnabledState.description: Indicates whether the state of object is enabled or disabled.

eltErpsAdminState.name: eltErpsAdminState
eltErpsAdminState.description: This object indicates the ERPS state of the bridge.

eltErpsLogState.name: eltErpsLogState
eltErpsLogState.description: This object indicates the ERPS log state of the bridge.

eltErpsTrapState.name: eltErpsTrapState
eltErpsTrapState.description: This object indicates the ERPS trap state of the bridge.

eltErpsPendingAction.name: eltErpsPendingAction
eltErpsPendingAction.description: The action to be done with the pending configuration. copyPendingActive - to copy the pending erps configuration to the active one. copyActivePending - to copy the active erps configuration to the pending one.

eltErpsPendingActionVlan.name: eltErpsPendingActionVlan
eltErpsPendingActionVlan.description: Variable is associated with eltErpsPendingAction and determines vlan_tag number in config for action copying/revert on pending config

eltErpsGetConfigId.name: eltErpsGetConfigId
eltErpsGetConfigId.description: Set config id fot snmp get.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSVlanTable.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSVlanTable
eltErpsMgmtRAPSVlanTable.description: This table contains ERPS ring configuration information.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSVlanEntry.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSVlanEntry
eltErpsMgmtRAPSVlanEntry.description: A list of ERPS ring configuration information.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSVlanId.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSVlanId
eltErpsMgmtRAPSVlanId.description: The RAPS VLAN is an index of configuration.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSWestPort.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSWestPort
eltErpsMgmtRAPSWestPort.description: This is one of the Ethernet ring ports. The value 0 indicates the west port is a virtual channel.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSWestPortState.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSWestPortState
eltErpsMgmtRAPSWestPortState.description: This is the west port state. It may change sometimes. When the west port is configured on a virtual channel, the west port state is always fowarding.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSEastPort.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSEastPort
eltErpsMgmtRAPSEastPort.description: This is the other Ethernet ring port. The value 0 indicates the west port is a virtual channel.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSEastPortState.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSEastPortState
eltErpsMgmtRAPSEastPortState.description: This is the east port state. It may change sometimes. When the east port is configured on a virtual channel, the east port state is always fowarding.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSRPLPort.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSRPLPort
eltErpsMgmtRAPSRPLPort.description: When the port Enable state is enabled, the RPL port's current port role is defined by the application of the ERPS.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerAdminState.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerAdminState
eltErpsMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerAdminState.description: The administrative value of the RPL owner state. The RPL owner is an Ethernet Ring Node adjacent to the RPL that is responsible for blocking its end of the RPL under normal conditions.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSRingMEL.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSRingMEL
eltErpsMgmtRAPSRingMEL.description: The ring MEL is the maintenance entity group (MEG) level providing a communication channel for ring automatic protection eltitching (RAPS) information.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSHoldOffTime.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSHoldOffTime
eltErpsMgmtRAPSHoldOffTime.description: In order to coordinate timing of protection eltitches at multiple layers.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSGuardTime.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSGuardTime
eltErpsMgmtRAPSGuardTime.description: This is used to prevent ring nodes from receiving outdated RAPS messages.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSWTRTime.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSWTRTime
eltErpsMgmtRAPSWTRTime.description: In the revertive mode of operation, to prevent frequent operation of the protection eltitch due to an intermittent defect, a failed working transport entity must become stable in a fault-free state.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSRingState.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSRingState
eltErpsMgmtRAPSRingState.description: This indicates the state of the ring: begin, init, idle, or protection.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSRingAdminState.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSRingAdminState
eltErpsMgmtRAPSRingAdminState.description: This indicates the administrative state of the ring.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerOperStatus.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerOperStatus
eltErpsMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerOperStatus.description: The current operational value of the RPL owner state. The value 'active' is used to indicate that the RPL owner administrative state is enabled and the device is operated as the active RPL owner. The value 'inactive' is used to indicate that the RPL owner administrative state is enabled, but the device is operated as the inactive RPL owner. The value 'disabled' is used to indicate that the RPL owner administrative state of the device is disabled.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList1t.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList1to1024
eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList1t.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (1-1024) that belongs to the protection VLANs.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList10.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList1025to2048
eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList10.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (1025-2048) that belongs to the protection VLANs.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList20.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList2049to3072
eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList20.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (2049-3072) that belongs to the protection VLANs.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList30.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList3073to4094
eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList30.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (3073-4094) that belongs to the protection VLANs.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtocolVersion.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtocolVersion
eltErpsMgmtRAPSProtocolVersion.description: This object indicates the ERPS protocol compatibility with other versions of ITU-T G.8032.

eltErpsMgmtRAPSRowStatus.name: eltErpsMgmtRAPSRowStatus
eltErpsMgmtRAPSRowStatus.description: This object indicates the RowStatus of this entry.

eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlTable.name: eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlTable
eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlTable.description: This table contains ERPS sub-ring configuration information.

eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlEntry.name: eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlEntry
eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlEntry.description: A list of ERPS sub-ring configuration information.

eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlRAPSVlanId.name: eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlRAPSVlanId
eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlRAPSVlanId.description: The RAPS VLAN is an index of configuration.

eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlSubRingRAPSVlanId.name: eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlSubRingRAPSVlanId
eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlSubRingRAPSVlanId.description: This indicates the ring control VLAN-ID of the sub-ring which connects to another ring.

eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlTCPropagationState.name: eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlTCPropagationState
eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlTCPropagationState.description: This indicates the state of sub-ring topology change propagation.

eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlRowStatus.name: eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlRowStatus
eltErpsMgmtSubRingCtrlRowStatus.description: This object indicates the RowStatus of this entry.

eltErpsSFDetectedTrap.name: eltErpsSFDetectedTrap
eltErpsSFDetectedTrap.description: When the signal fail occurs, a trap will be generated.

eltErpsSFClearedTrap.name: eltErpsSFClearedTrap
eltErpsSFClearedTrap.description: When the signal fail clears, a trap will be generated.

eltErpsRPLOwnerConflictTrap.name: eltErpsRPLOwnerConflictTrap
eltErpsRPLOwnerConflictTrap.description: When a conflict occurs, a trap will be generated.

eltErpsNodeId.name: eltErpsNodeId
eltErpsNodeId.description: This used trap object means the node MAC.
